prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Cream Smoke City Manga Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules: Use a clean surreal editorial manga poster look with off-white paper space, warm cream organic masses, pale gray hatching, thin black contour linework, precise miniature architecture, and one muted teal flat framing shape. Keep the main subject large and close-cropped, with the biggest visual drama coming from nested curls, puffs, droplets, and tiny floating fragments. Keep depth shallow and poster-like, with soft ambient lighting, small stipple patches, clean edge control, and no cinematic realism. If text is requested, use only tiny hand-drawn signage or microcopy integrated into buildings or props.

Avoid: photorealism, 3D render, glossy anime still, painterly fantasy art, western superhero comic style, large slogan typography, copied faces, copied clothing, copied city layout, copied wave shape, watermarks, signatures, logos, platform UI, QR codes, neon glow, heavy gradients, muddy grit, accidental digital noise.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
